                    <br /> <div>- Germany was actually the first country to produce a rocket capable of crossing the boundary of space. The famed V2 rocket of World War II was a ballistic missile launched by the Nazis on England and Belgium.</div>
                    <br /> <div>- The Lewis Research Center attempted to develop diamond-hard coatings for aerospace systems, later creating a tehnique that was developed and patented for just that purpose. This is the origin of the scratch-resistent lenses.</div>
                    <br /> <div>- Infant formulas now contain a nutritional enrichment ingredients, the origins of which can be traced back to NASA-sponsored research that explored the use of algae for long duration space travel.   </div>
                    <br /> <div>- Water is used to reduce extreme heat and energy generated by a rocket launch. During a launch, the water deluge system releases approximately 450,000 gallons of water up to 100 feet in the air.</div>
